{
  "_README": {
    "purpose": "SUPERSET OpenRouter registry wired by default via OPENROUTER_MODELS_CONFIG_PATH in .mcp.json. PAL loads exactly ONE registry file and REPLACES its bundled one (providers/registries/base.py:42-44), so this file must contain BOTH PAL's bundled models AND our GLM overlay — otherwise the other models would lose their correct context windows.",
    "why_glm": "The plugin's headline feature is GLM-5.2 at its full 1,048,576-token window. Without this file GLM falls back to PAL's generic ~32K (providers/openrouter.py:_lookup_capabilities), capping per-call file budget to ~3.5K tokens. With 1M declared here, per-call file budget becomes ~268K (window x0.8 content x0.4 files x0.8 guard; utils/model_context.py + utils/file_utils.py:843-850).",
    "provenance": "The 27 base models are copied VERBATIM from PAL's bundled conf/openrouter_models.json at upstream commit 7afc7c1cc96e23992c8f105f960132c657883bb1 (pal-mcp-server 9.8.2). .mcp.json pins PAL to our fork sergiobe31/pal-mcp-server (branch openrouter-reasoning) = that upstream commit + a reasoning patch that does NOT touch the bundled registry, so this copy still cannot drift against the registry PAL ships.",
    "reasoning_policy": "Only z-ai/glm-5.2 has supports_extended_thinking:true, so by default only GLM gets OpenRouter reasoning (the fork maps PAL thinking_mode -> reasoning effort; max -> xhigh). The other 11 reasoning-capable OpenRouter models were intentionally set to false here so the shipped default is GLM-only and byte-identical to upstream for them. Flip any model's flag to true to enable reasoning for it.",
    "resync_instructions": "When you bump the PAL SHA in .mcp.json, re-sync this file: re-run the generator against the new commit's conf/openrouter_models.json and re-append the z-ai/glm-5.2 entry (always the last item below). That is the single, reviewable moment where drift could enter.",
    "glm_entry_verified": "z-ai/glm-5.2 confirmed on OpenRouter /api/v1/models: single slug, context_length 1,048,576, no separate [1m] variant. Verified 2026-06-30.",
